"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385627","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-06-29","<p>How Sahared Services Connected Limited manage their workforce is an operational issue for them as employers. Newport Shared Services staff are no longer civil servants.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2015-06-29T16:55:40.84Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385627/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385627/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385627/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-06-24","Shared Services Connected: Newport","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what assurance he has received from Steria that work and jobs at the Newport shared services centre will not be off-shored.","false","Biography information for Jessica Morden","Newport East","Jessica Morden","4076"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385628","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-07-08","<p>The Government is working together with the Offshore Wind Industry to build a competitive and innovative UK supply chain that delivers and sustains jobs, exports and economic benefit for the UK.</p><p>Officials are working with the Developers, who were successful in the first Contract for Difference (CFD) allocation round, on the implementation of their Supply Chain Plan and to boost UK content.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-07-08T13:07:06.803Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385628/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385628/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385628/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-06-24","Wind Power: Seas and Oceans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, pursuant to the Answer of 4 June 2015 to Question 603, what steps her Department is taking to ensure that the UK supply chain benefits from investment in the offshore wind industry.","false","Biography information for Harry Harpham","Sheffield, Brightside and Hillsborough","Harry Harpham","3934"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386390","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-06-30","<p>Rebalancing the economy by creating a Northern Powerhouse is part of our long-term economic plan, to pool its strengths and become greater than the sum of its parts. This could add £44bn to the Northern Economy by 2030, or £1,600 per person living there -in real terms. Our £20 million investment in Health North will make a valuable contribution to these efforts.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Complimenting this, on 1<sup>st</sup> June my Rt hon Friend the Chancellor of the Exchequer announced proposals for making the Midlands an Engine of Growth. Working with Local Enterprise Partnerships across the Midlands, we are seeking to align investments and devolve decision-making, to create the strongest possible environment for economic growth across the region.</p><p> </p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman",,"2015-06-30T14:49:49.597Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386390/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386390/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386390/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-06-24","Regional Planning and Development: North of England","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what recent steps he has taken to promote regional growth and create a Northern Powerhouse.","false","Biography information for James Morris","Halesowen and Rowley Regis","James Morris","900646"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386391","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-06-30","<p>The Office for Budget Responsibility make forecasts for net trade and GDP, and will be updating these on the 8<sup>th</sup> July. Exports and imports made up 28.3% and 30.3% of GDP in 2014. However, trade has wider economic benefits than through net trade, as it indirectly boost growth through increasing competition, innovation and efficiency of UK firms.</p><p> </p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2015-06-30T16:14:23.197Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386391/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386391/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386391/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-06-24","Trade","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what forecast he has made of the contribution of net trade to GDP in the next four years.","false","Biography information for Susan Elan Jones","Clwyd South","Susan Elan Jones","900645"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386392","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-06-30","<p>We help to provide small businesses with access to the finance they need, expert business advice and export support. British Business Bank programmes are supporting £1.8bn of finance to over 40,000 smaller businesses, with a further £1.4bn of finance to mid-cap businesses.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The <em>Business Growth Service</em> provides support to firms with growth potential. <em>Growth Hubs </em>join up local resources to provide local support. And 48,000 businesses have been helped to export through our UK Trade and Investment support – of those, 90% were small businesses.</p><p> </p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-06-30T16:05:55.857Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386392/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386392/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386392/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-06-24","Small Businesses","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what recent support he has provided to small businesses.","false","Biography information for Daniel Kawczynski","Shrewsbury and Atcham","Daniel Kawczynski","900648"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386393","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-06-30","<p>I would like to welcome the new hon Member for Ilford North to this House and commend him for his commitment to student welfare as former president of the National Union of Students.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>We have and will continue to have a world class HE system.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>To deliver our commitment to reduce the deficit, we are reviewing all BIS spend as part of our preparations for the Spending Review. We will ensure the continuing success and stability of our reforms to University funding, so that the interests of both students and taxpayers are fairly represented.</p><p> </p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2015-06-30T16:16:14.78Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386393/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386393/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386393/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-06-24","Students: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what plans he has to change the terms and conditions for higher education student finance.","false","Biography information for Wes Streeting","Ilford North","Wes Streeting","900643"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386394","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-06-30","<p>The Government believes high standards of corporate governance promote the trust and confidence in business needed to facilitate trade, investment, prosperity and long-term growth.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>In the last Parliament we took significant steps to reform corporate governance including improving corporate reporting and updating the rules on disqualification of directors.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>This Government will continue to work to ensure the corporate governance framework fosters trust in UK companies and encourages long-term investment.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2015-06-30T16:13:06.053Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386394/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386394/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386394/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-06-24","Companies: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what steps he is taking to encourage improvements in corporate governance.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","900650"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386395","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-06-30","<p>All future spending decisions will be taken as part of the Spending Review.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>In the last 5 years, we have increased funding for apprenticeships whilst cutting the overall level of the adult skills budget as a contribution to deficit reduction.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2015-06-30T16:22:25.27Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386395/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386395/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386395/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-06-24","Adult Education: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what steps he is taking to maintain the adult skills funding budget.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","900654"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386396","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-06-30","<p>We are focused on increasing the number of jobs at all levels of skill and on investing in 3 million apprenticeships, which will help people to improve their skills and command higher wages.</p><p> </p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2015-06-30T16:17:17.203Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386396/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386396/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386396/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-06-24","Employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what recent estimate he has made of the proportion of jobs in the economy which are low-skilled.","false","Biography information for Jeff Smith","Manchester, Withington","Jeff Smith","900651"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386397","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-06-30","<p>Catapult centres are opening up opportunities for companies of all sizes throughout the UK and across sectors from Satellites to Transport, and Energy to Cell Therapy.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>My Rt hon Friend the Minister for Small Business, Industry and Enterprise recently opened the new Aerospace Manufacturing Technology Centre in Coventry – which will create supply chain opportunities in this successful UK sector.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>This Government is committed to creating more Catapults to bring further growth to other sectors across the country.</p><p> </p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2015-06-30T16:11:18.143Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386397/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386397/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386397/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-06-24","Technology and Innovation Centres","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what recent progress Catapult Centres have made on creating opportunities for business in high-profile markets.","false","Biography information for Peter Aldous","Waveney","Peter Aldous","900647"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386398","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-06-30","<p>The Government is clear that all large companies should trade fairly with small suppliers.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>That is why we will shortly consult on proposals to establish a Small Business Conciliation Service to help small businesses resolve disputes.</p><p> </p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2015-06-30T16:07:40.337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386398/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386398/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/386398/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-06-24","Business","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what steps he plans to take to encourage large businesses to trade more fairly with small businesses.","false","Biography information for Heidi Allen","South Cambridgeshire","Heidi Allen","900652"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384835","Attorney General","false","2015-06-29","<p>The Crown Prosecution Service (CPS) does not maintain a central record of the number of cases which were not able to proceed as a result of identifiable errors by the CPS. Obtaining this information would require a manual review of individual case files which would incur a disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p>","South Swindon","Robert Buckland",,"2015-06-29T13:01:34.48Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384835/answer","Biography information for Robert Buckland","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384835/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384835/answer",,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2015-06-23","Administration of Justice","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, what estimate he has made of the number of cases which were not able to proceed to their conclusion in (a) Magistrates' and (b) Crown courts as a result of identifiable errors by the Crown Prosecution Service in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","3678"
