"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384865","Department of Health","false","2015-07-01","<p>Data are not collected centrally for those diagnosed with problems relating to alcohol consumption. Drinking alcohol can lead to more than 60 different medical conditions, many of these conditions can be a result of long term alcohol misuse.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2015-07-01T11:48:30.167Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384865/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384865/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384865/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-06-23","Alcoholism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many people have been diagnosed with problems relating to alcohol consumption in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","3753"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384866","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-06-29","<p>My Department will publish proposals for consultation in due course, including an impact assessment on which we will welcome comments.</p><p> </p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2015-06-29T14:42:01.263Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384866/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384866/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384866/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-06-23","Voluntary Work: Leave","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, when he will bring forward plans to give staff an additional three days of paid leave for volunteering; what estimate he has made of the potential cost of this policy to the (a) private sector and (b) public sector; and how many staff in the (i) private sector and (ii) public sector would be granted such additional paid leave.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","3855"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384867","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-30","<p>The Government has been consistent and clear that its objective in respect of RBS ownership is to return the bank to the private sector in full.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>This policy is supported by recent advice from the Governor of the Bank of England that “it is in the public interest for the Government to begin now to return RBS to the private sector”, and that “there could be considerable net costs to taxpayers of further delaying the start of a sale”. The findings of the recently published Rothschild report into the Government’s shareholding in RBS concur with this assessment.</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2015-06-30T14:12:43.54Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384867/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384867/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384867/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-23","Royal Bank of Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the cost and benefits of (a) converting Royal Bank of Scotland (RBS) into a network of local stakeholder banks, (b) breaking up RBS into a series of challenger banks, (c) converting RBS into a state-owned business bank and (d) other options for the future of RBS considered by his Department; and if he will place a copy of any such assessments in the Library.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","3801"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384868","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-29","<p>The Government takes the firm view that consumers must be able to easily access clear and transparent information about their accounts with banks and other financial service companies.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Government is continuing to drive forward a wide-reaching and ambitious programme of reforms to open up competition in the banking sector, including enabling innovation in the use of bank data so that customers are able to use online information more effectively. This includes initiatives like the Midata current account tool, which will help customers switch to the best current account for them.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Financial Conduct Authority is also currently reviewing cost-cutting initiatives that affect a significant number of customers, including the withdrawal of paper statements.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2015-06-29T13:52:21.423Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384868/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384868/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384868/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-23","Consumers: Billing","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will take steps to ensure that consumers are given the choice to receive bills, statements and other important information on paper from their financial service providers without charge.","false","Biography information for Andrew Bridgen","North West Leicestershire","Andrew Bridgen","3793"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384869","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-30","<p>The Chancellor has previously set out his objectives for the banks in state ownership, including Royal Bank of Scotland. We want to maximise the ability of these important banks to support the British economy, and we want to get the best value for money for the taxpayer.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Large scale public ownership has an inhibiting effect on the involvement of private institutions in a company such as RBS, and therefore naturally impacts on broader commercial performance. The best way to deliver our objectives is to return RBS to private ownership. Commercial organisations are more efficient, more innovative and more effective when they are in the private sector.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>This policy is supported by advice from the Governor of the Bank of England and independent analysis from Rothschild investment bank. In their recent report into this issue, Rothschild note that by starting to sell down its stake in RBS, “the Government can bring about broader benefits for the institution, which could help to accelerate its recovery”, as well as improving the share price and securing value for the taxpayer.</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2015-06-30T14:20:21.953Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384869/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384869/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384869/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-23","Royal Bank of Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, with reference to the oral statement by the Economic Secretary to the Treasury of 11 June 2015, Official Report, column 1373, what the evidence base is for his statement that the Royal Bank of Scotland has not been able to play its full part in small and medium-sized enterprise lending because of public ownership.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","3794"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384871","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-30","<p>The government inherited a taper system withdrawing the personal allowance for those on incomes above £100,000 from the Labour government.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The government has also inherited the largest deficit in post-war history due to unsustainable increases in government spending by the Labour government and the effects of the financial crisis. Because of this exceptional challenge we have been unable to remove the personal allowance taper to date. The government’s focus has been on helping low and middle income earners.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>However, the government has committed to raising the higher rate threshold to £50,000 by the end of this parliament. This will lower taxes for middle and high income earners as it will increase the point before individuals start paying 40% income tax. The government wants to reduce the amount of income tax that people pay and rewarding those who want to work hard and progress.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2015-06-30T15:47:16.777Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384871/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384871/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384871/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-23","Income Tax: Tax Allowances","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what plans he has to reinstate the full personal tax allowance for individuals earning in excess of £100,000 per year.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","3724"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384872","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-30","<p>HM Revenue and Customs does not publish figures for Working Tax Credits or Child Tax Credits broken down by region.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2015-06-30T09:53:10.017Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384872/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384872/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384872/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-23","Welfare Tax Credits: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the cost to the public purse was of (a) working tax credits and (b) child tax credit for claimants in Northern Ireland in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Baroness Ritchie of Downpatrick","South Down","Ms Margaret Ritchie","3841"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384873","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-02","<p>Information detailing the number of recipient families of (a) Working Tax Credits and (b) Child Tax Credits for the local authority of Liverpool and the parliamentary constituency of Liverpool Riverside can be found at the following location: <br> <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/personal-tax-credits-statistics" target="_blank">gov.uk/government/collections/personal-tax-credits-statistics</a>. <br> <strong><br> </strong></p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","3889","2015-07-02T15:09:04.267Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384873/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384873/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384873/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-23","Working Tax Credit: Liverpool","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many recipients of working tax credit there are in (a) Liverpool and (b) Liverpool Riverside constituency.","false","Biography information for Dame Louise Ellman","Liverpool, Riverside","Mrs Louise Ellman","3888"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384874","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-02","<p>Information detailing the number of recipient families of (a) Working Tax Credits and (b) Child Tax Credits for the local authority of Liverpool and the parliamentary constituency of Liverpool Riverside can be found at the following location: <br> <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/personal-tax-credits-statistics" target="_blank">gov.uk/government/collections/personal-tax-credits-statistics</a>. <br> <strong><br> </strong></p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","3888","2015-07-02T15:09:04.36Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384874/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384874/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384874/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-23","Child Tax Credit: Liverpool","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many recipients of child tax credit there are in (a) Liverpool and (b) Liverpool Riverside constituency.","false","Biography information for Dame Louise Ellman","Liverpool, Riverside","Mrs Louise Ellman","3889"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384875","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-30","<p>The failure of IT infrastructure at Royal Bank of Scotland, or any other bank on which customers rely to manage their money, is completely unacceptable. Responsibility for infrastructure in the UK financial sector is primarily for the firms themselves. However, financial regulators have a role to play in supervising, coordinating and driving change to improve the operational resilience of the sector.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Financial Conduct Authority (FCA) and Prudential Regulation Authority (PRA) jointly launched, in October 2014, a review of firms’ critical infrastructure and technology resilience. The review focuses on the most significant UK retail deposit-taking organisations, and is expected to conclude later this summer. The results will not be published, but the FCA and PRA will provide feedback to the firms individually on their findings and agree any follow-up actions.</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2015-06-30T14:21:17.06Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384875/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384875/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384875/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-23","Banks","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what discussions he has had with (a) the Royal Bank of Scotland and (b) Ulster Bank on steps to assist with any potential future problems with their critical infrastructure.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","3630"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384876","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-30","<p>The government announced on 17 June that it will launch a consultation to look at making the process for transferring pensions from one scheme to another quicker and smoother, including, if there is sufficient evidence, options to address excessive early exit penalties. The Financial Conduct Authority will, in parallel, gather information from pension providers to establish an evidence base for action in this area. This is part of a wider programme of action by government and regulators to ensure that consumers can take advantage of the new pensions freedoms, introduced in April.</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2015-06-30T14:24:32.53Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384876/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384876/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384876/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-23","Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether the forthcoming consultation on a charge cap for savers withdrawing their money from pensions will include a proposal for a charge cap on income drawdown products.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","3643"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384877","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-30","<p>HMRC do not plan to collect data on the length of time taken to process Working Tax Credit claims.</p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2015-06-30T13:26:44.15Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384877/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384877/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384877/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-23","Working Tax Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, pursuant to the Answer of 26 March 2015 to Question 228908, if he will make it his policy to collect data on the length of time taken to process working tax credit claims.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","3663"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384878","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-30","<p>The UK’s monetary policy framework, set out in the Bank of England Act 1998, gives operational responsibility for monetary policy to the independent Monetary Policy Committee. The Chancellor of the Exchequer has frequent discussions with the Governor of the Bank of England on a wide range of issues relating to the UK economy.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2015-06-30T13:59:26.923Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384878/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384878/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384878/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-23","Interest Rates","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what recent discussions he has had with the Governor of the Bank of England on the likelihood that interest ratios will remain at their present level.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","3629"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384879","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-30","<p>No such estimate has been made.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2015-06-30T15:52:44.7Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384879/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384879/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384879/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-23","Self-employed","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate he has made of savings accruing to the Exchequer from changes in the level of self employment in the last three years.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","3706"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384881","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-01","<p>The Northern Powerhouse is based on the idea - supported by economic theory - that through pooling the individual strengths of the cities, towns and regions of the North we can achieve a reduction in the economic disparity between London and the North.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2015-07-01T15:51:47.853Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384881/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384881/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384881/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-23","Regional Planning and Development: North of England","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the geographical boundaries are of the Northern Powerhouse.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","3704"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384883","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-01","<p>Data for the mean gross annual pay by region are in the Office for National Statistics publication, &quot;the Annual Survey of Hours and Earnings, 2014&quot;:http://www.ons.gov.uk/ons/publications/re-reference-tables.html?edition=tcm%3A77-337425</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2015-07-01T15:56:36.037Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384883/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384883/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384883/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-23","Personal Income: North of England","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what the average annual income is of each person living in the area covered by the Northern Powerhouse.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","3705"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384884","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-30","<p>The UK is at the forefront of multilateral action through the G20 and the OECD to reform the international tax rules.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The UK used its Presidency of the G8 to successfully build international support for a common template for Country-by-Country reporting of tax and other financial information to tax authorities, which we have legislated to implement in line with the international agreement. We continue to play a leading role in the OECD Base Erosion and Profit Shifting (BEPS) project to ensure that profits are taxed where the economic activities that give rise to them are located.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>We are also actively engaged in discussions within the EU on tax transparency and ways the EU can build on OECD work in order to ensure a coherent and effective international approach to these issues.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2015-06-30T15:51:16.593Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384884/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384884/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384884/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-23","Taxation: Conferences","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will discuss with his international counterparts the prospects for organising an international fair tax summit.","false","Biography information for Stewart Malcolm McDonald","Glasgow South","Stewart McDonald","3682"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384885","HM Treasury","false","2015-06-29","<p>The issues raised are a matter for the Financial Ombudsman Service (FOS) who are operationally independent from Government.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>These questions have been passed on to the FOS. The FOS will reply directly to the honourable member by letter. A copy of the letter will be placed in the Library of the House.</p><p> </p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2015-06-29T13:54:17.26Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384885/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384885/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384885/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-23","Endowment Mortgages: Misrepresentation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what information he holds on how many complaints have been received by the Financial Services Ombudsman relating to compensation for the mis-selling of endowment mortgages; what proportion of those complaints has been resolved; and what the average time taken to reach a resolution of those complaints was.","false","Biography information for Helen Jones","Warrington North","Helen Jones","3871"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384886","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-29","<p>The savings from the abolition of the Percentage Threshold Scheme (PTS) of £52M 2014/15 were reinvested to set up Fit for Work and provide a tax exemption of up to £500 per year per employee for medical treatments recommended by Fit for Work or an employer arranged occupational health service. This was based on an independent review[1] into sickness absence which found that PTS provided little incentive to tackle the causes of sickness absence and recommended the new approach.</p><p> </p><p>[1] Dame Carol Black and David Frost conducted an independent review in November 2011 of sickness absence in the UK</p><p><a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/181060/health-at-work.pdf" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/181060/health-at-work.pdf</a></p><p> </p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-06-29T17:05:33.263Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384886/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384886/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384886/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-23","Statutory Sick Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate he made of savings accruing to the Exchequer from changes to the percentage threshold scheme for statutory sick pay scheme introduced on 6 April 2014.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","3835"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384887","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-07-01","<p>National guidance is clear that the potential effect of a new residential development being located close to an existing business giving rise to noise should be carefully considered.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2015-07-01T15:55:56.183Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384887/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384887/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384887/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-06-23","Licensed Premises: Noise","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, with reference to the guidance set out in National Planning Policy Guidance, paragraph 006 ID 30-006-20141224, what assessment his Department has made of the effect of changes introduced in December 2014 to that guidance on the ability of long-standing entertainment venues to ensure that new developments in their vicinity undertake appropriate sound mitigation measures.","false","Biography information for Kerry McCarthy","Bristol East","Kerry McCarthy","3922"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384888","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-07-01","<p>Elements of the Agent of Change principle already exist within planning policies and guidance. The planning guidance supporting the Framework is clear that the potential effect of a new residential development being located close to an existing business giving rise to noise should be carefully considered. The guidance underlines planning’s contribution to avoiding future complaints and risks to local business from resulting enforcement action. To help avoid such situations, local councils are encouraged to consider appropriate mitigation including designing the new development to reduce the impact of noise from the local environment and optimising the sound insulation provided by the building envelope.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2015-07-01T15:54:58.823Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384888/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384888/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384888/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-06-23","Licensed Premises: Noise","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, if he will make it his policy to introduce an agent of change principle into existing planning law regulations to ensure that pre-existing pubs and entertainment venues are not adversely affected by noise nuisance regulations when new residential units are created close to their business.","false","Biography information for Richard Fuller","Bedford","Richard Fuller","3838"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384890","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-07-01","<p>Local authorities reported that there were 330 applicant households headed by 16 and 17 year olds in temporary accommodation arranged by authorities at 31 March 2015. This compares to 3,140 when this data was first collected in 2007. This is the only information reported on young people from households in temporary accommodation. No figures are held on the numbers in accommodation provided by the voluntary sector.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2015-07-01T15:50:30.033Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384890/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384890/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384890/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-06-23","Temporary Accommodation: Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what recent estimate he has made of the number of young people who are living in emergency or temporary accommodation provided by (a) local authorities and (b) the voluntary sector.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","3816"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384891","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-08","<p /> <p>We will publish a full Impact Assessment in due course.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-07-08T09:59:51.597Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384891/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384891/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384891/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-23","Homelessness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate he has made of the effect on the levels of homelessness from the proposed reduction in the benefit cap to £23,000 each year; and what research was undertaken to calculate this estimate.","false","Biography information for Mr Clive Betts","Sheffield South East","Mr Clive Betts","3677"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384892","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-07-01","<p>By law local authorities have a duty to provide advice and information to anyone asking for help. <br><br>To help them discharge that important duty, we have, among other sources of support, provided £10 million funding to the National Homelessness Advice service to support frontline staff, and introduced the £8 million Help for Single Homeless Fund which will help 22,000 people in 168 areas across England by April 2016.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2015-07-01T15:45:58.25Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384892/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384892/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384892/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-06-23","Homelessness: Single People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what steps the Government has taken to ensure that local councils provide adequate support and assistance to single homeless people when they approach their council for help.","false","Biography information for Stuart Andrew","Pudsey","Stuart Andrew","3795"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384893","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-07-01","<p>Information about local authority expenditure is collected on the Revenue forms. In order to reduce burden to local authorities, only grants over £200 million are recorded individually; all other grants (below £200 million) are aggregated within &quot;other grants&quot;.</p><p> </p><p>Shopmobility grant funding information is not held centrally. Information on all grants expenditure should be published in a local authority's Statement of Accounts and published on their website.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2015-07-01T15:44:25.577Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384893/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384893/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384893/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-06-23","Shopmobility: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many local authorities have provided grant funding to Shopmobility schemes in each of the last three years; and what the level of such grants awarded was by each such local authority.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","3805"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384894","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-06-30","<p>Sport England set out to invest £1.1 million in British Shooting between 2013-17. British Shooting has a number of programmes encouraging participation including “Get on Target”. It is also working in partnership with the Council for Cadet Rifle Shooting and the Scouts Association. UK Sport supports both Olympic and Paralympic Shooting disciplines, with investment in both for the 2016 Rio Olympics and Paralympics.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2015-06-30T11:32:29.39Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384894/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384894/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384894/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-06-23","Gun Sports: Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what steps he is taking to encourage young people to take up shooting sports.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","3631"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384895","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-06-30","<p>I am keenly aware of the importance of coverage of the EU referendum by our broadcasters being impartial and balanced. I have asked the BBC Trust, major commercial broadcasters, and Ofcom to consider the need for the broadcasting regulatory structure to ensure this impartiality is delivered.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-06-30T09:33:43.157Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384895/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384895/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384895/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-06-23","BBC: UK Membership of EU","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, if he will discuss with the BBC Trust what steps it plans to take to monitor how the BBC fulfils its campaign on the duty of impartiality during the forthcoming referendum on the UK's EU membership.","false","Biography information for Mr Philip Hollobone","Kettering","Mr Philip Hollobone","3644"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384896","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-06-30","<p>This Government believes local newspapers have a vital role to play in local communities and in local democracy. We are keen to explore how local newspapers can achieve a long term sustainable future and Government has already committed to consulting on business rates relief for local newspapers, as well as committing almost £1 million to support 24 pilot projects on the future of statutory notices.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey","3861","2015-06-30T09:32:47.67Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384896/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384896/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384896/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-06-23","Local Press","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what steps he is taking to support local newspapers; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Vicky Foxcroft","Lewisham, Deptford","Vicky Foxcroft","3860"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384898","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2015-06-30","<p>This Government believes local newspapers have a vital role to play in local communities and in local democracy. We are keen to explore how local newspapers can achieve a long term sustainable future and Government has already committed to consulting on business rates relief for local newspapers, as well as committing almost £1 million to support 24 pilot projects on the future of statutory notices.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey","3860","2015-06-30T09:32:47.767Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384898/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384898/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384898/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-06-23","Local Press","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what steps he is taking to encourage publishing groups to support local papers; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Vicky Foxcroft","Lewisham, Deptford","Vicky Foxcroft","3861"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384899","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-29","<p>I have nothing further to add to the answer I gave on 22 June 2015 to Question 3007.</p><p> </p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2015-06-29T15:19:25.57Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384899/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384899/answer","HOC 3867 Hansard Extracts.doc","Ministry of Defence: Cost Effectiveness","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384899/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-23","Ministry of Defence: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 22 June 2015, to Question 3007, when he will announce further details of by how much running costs will be reduced on (a) consultants, (b) overtime and travel, (c) re-profiting of equipment and (d) infrastructure spend in 2015-16; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","3867"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384900","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-29","<p>The information requested in relation to school fees is provided in the table below. Information relating to individual schools could be provided only at disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><p>Continuity of Education (CEA) allowance is provided to assist Service personnel to achieve continuity of education for their children that would otherwise be denied if their children accompanied them on frequent and consecutive assignments. These payments are made by the Ministry of Defence to individual Service personnel claimants, and not to the educational establishments/schools attended by the children to whom the claims relate.</p><p> </p><p>The coalition Government reviewed this scheme as part of the Strategic Defence and Security Review and in December 2010 made changes which have delivered savings of £20 million each year and an associated reduction in claimants compared to the cost of the scheme as inherited in 2010.</p><p> </p><p>Spend by financial year on CEA including special educational needs supplement and payment of income tax liability.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Financial Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>FY 2009-10</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>FY 2010-11</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>FY 2011-12</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>FY 2012-13</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>FY 2013-14</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>FY 2014-15</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Cost</p><p>(£ million)</p></td><td><p>110.9</p></td><td><p>114.5</p></td><td><p>110.8</p></td><td><p>98.9</p></td><td><p>89.3</p></td><td><p>84.5</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Claimants</p></td><td><p>6,020</p></td><td><p>6,090</p></td><td><p>5,680</p></td><td><p>4,950</p></td><td><p>4,300</p></td><td><p>3,880</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2015-06-29T15:24:29.447Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384900/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384900/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384900/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-23","Armed Forces: Private Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how much his Department has spent on private school fees for the families of armed forces personnel in each year since 2010; and how much his Department has spent on each such educational establishment in that time.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","3879"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384901","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-29","<p>The following makes and models of allocated and pool cars are provided by the Department for senior military personnel and Ministers: Ford Galaxy, Ford Mondeo, Honda Accord, Honda Civic, Skoda Superb, Toyota Avensis and Volkswagen Passat.</p><p> </p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-06-29T15:18:50.717Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384901/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384901/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384901/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-23","Ministry of Defence: Official Cars","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the make and model is of each of the official cars his Department provides for (a) senior military personnel and (b) Ministers.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","3667"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384902","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-06-29","<p>Information on the origin of meat and poultry purchased is not held by the Ministry of Defence (MOD).</p><p>MOD personnel in the UK and permanent bases overseas are served through a number of catering contracts. Armed Forces personnel serving on operations, overseas exercises and on Her Majesty's Ships are catered for under a single food contract with Purple Foodservice Solutions Ltd.</p><p>Purple Foodservice list approximately 1,150 different food-related items for the Armed Forces in the core range price list. Currently, they estimate that approximately 60% of lines listed, excluding fresh produce, are sourced from suppliers within the UK.</p><p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 4 June 2013 (Official Report, column 1116W) to the hon. Member for Richmond Park (Zac Goldsmith).</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2015-06-29T16:36:09.687Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384902/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384902/answer","20130604_Hansard_extract_Armed_Forces_Food.doc","20130604 - Hansard extract on Armed Foeces Food","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/384902/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-06-23","Ministry of Defence: Meat Products","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the source of origin is of the meat and poultry products procured by his Department.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","3666"
