"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385028","Department of Health","false","2015-06-29","<p>Timing for access to care or treatments for all NHS England service specifications or policies is based on an assessment of the evidence for clinical effectiveness, cost effectiveness and affordability.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2015-06-29T16:04:43.887Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385028/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385028/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385028/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-06-23","Viral Diseases","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, on what basis his Department decided the national waiting time criteria for referral to (a) specialist services for HIV treatment and (b) hepatitis C treatment; and what the reason is for the difference in duration between the two sets of criteria.","false","Biography information for Liz McInnes","Heywood and Middleton","Liz McInnes","3905"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385029","Department of Health","false","2015-06-29","<p>These are matters for the local National Health Service.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>We are advised that there are challenges for both commissioners and providers in South East London which are linked to increasing demand for services. The six South East London Clinical Commissioning Groups and NHS England are working closely with local authorities, providers and local people and patients to develop a strategy under the programme <em>Our Healthier South East London</em> to deliver improvements across a number of priorities and address these challenges.</p><p> </p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","3863","2015-06-29T16:11:51.913Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385029/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385029/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385029/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-06-23","Hospitals: Greater London","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what recent assessment he has made of the financial and clinical performance of (a) Lewisham and Greenwich, (b) King's College Hospital and (c) Guy's and St Thomas' hospital trusts.","false","Biography information for Heidi Alexander","Lewisham East","Heidi Alexander","3878"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385030","Department of Health","false","2015-06-29","<p>We understand that there is a capital project underway at the Foundation Trust to improve emergency care for patients. This is a £20 million project to create an Emergency Floor at St Thomas’ hospital which is due to be completed in the latter part of 2016. This will help develop a new service model for emergency care that will transform not only the accident and emergency (A&amp;E) departments but also acute medical wards which patients are admitted to from A&amp;E.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2015-06-29T16:09:13.137Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385030/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385030/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385030/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-06-23","Guy's and St Thomas' NHS Foundation Trust","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what recent discussions he has had with Guy's and St Thomas' NHS Foundation Trust on expanding capacity within its accident and emergency and maternity departments.","false","Biography information for Heidi Alexander","Lewisham East","Heidi Alexander","3877"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385031","Department of Health","false","2015-06-29","<p>These are matters for the local National Health Service.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>We are advised that there are challenges for both commissioners and providers in South East London which are linked to increasing demand for services. The six South East London Clinical Commissioning Groups and NHS England are working closely with local authorities, providers and local people and patients to develop a strategy under the programme <em>Our Healthier South East London</em> to deliver improvements across a number of priorities and address these challenges.</p><p> </p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","3878","2015-06-29T16:11:51.827Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385031/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385031/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385031/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-06-23","Health Services: Greater London","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what recent assessment he has made of the financial sustainability of NHS services in south east London.","false","Biography information for Heidi Alexander","Lewisham East","Heidi Alexander","3863"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385032","Department of Health","false","2015-06-29","<p>The Trust Special Administrator’s (TSA) regime was first introduced in the Health Act 2009 and is a distinct statutory process intended to be used as a last resort to address significant, intractable failings at a National Health Service trust or foundation trust in a time-bound and transparent way.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>There are no current recommendations to place any trusts into the TSA regime.</p><p> </p>","Ipswich","Ben Gummer",,"2015-06-29T15:11:32.587Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385032/answer","Biography information for Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385032/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385032/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-06-23","NHS Trusts: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what estimate he has made of the number of NHS trusts that will be put into the unsustainable providers regime in the next five years in (a) England and (b) London.","false","Biography information for Heidi Alexander","Lewisham East","Heidi Alexander","3864"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385033","Department of Health","false","2015-07-01","<p>This information in is not collected. Whilst National Health Service programme budgeting data captures information within the category ‘<em>problems of the musculoskeletal system’ </em>spend on back pain is not identified. Some back pain treatment costs are captured through NHS reference costs data, but because the vast majority of back pain treatment activity is not inpatient care, these costs are do not reflect the total cost.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2015-07-01T11:46:05.423Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385033/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385033/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385033/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-06-23","Back Pain","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, if he will estimate the cost to the NHS of treating back pain in each of the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Andrew Stephenson","Pendle","Andrew Stephenson","3829"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385034","Department of Health","false","2015-06-29","<p>National Health Service organisations are best placed to decide how many staff they employ. Services should be tailored to meet the needs of their patients and local communities, to deliver safe care. For the first time we have published ward by ward staffing information so patients and NHS leaders have this available as part of our transparency drive. Where there are concerns, the Chief Inspector of Hospitals will take action.</p><p> </p>","Ipswich","Ben Gummer",,"2015-06-29T15:18:53.637Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385034/answer","Biography information for Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385034/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385034/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-06-23","Hospitals: Greater London","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what recent assessment he has made of the ability of hospitals in London to meet the London quality staffing standards for (a) maternity, (b) A&E and (c) paediatric care.","false","Biography information for Heidi Alexander","Lewisham East","Heidi Alexander","3865"
