"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385151","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-29","<p>The information requested by Parliamentary constituency is not readily available and could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-06-29T13:52:26.553Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385151/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385151/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385151/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-23","Employment and Support Allowance: Preston","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people in Preston constituency who applied for employment and support allowance in (a) December 2014 and (b) January 2015 (i) have had medical assessments and (ii) are still waiting for medical assessments.","false","Biography information for Sir Mark Hendrick","Preston","Mr Mark Hendrick","3669"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385152","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-29","<p /> <p>The table below shows the number of claimants who registered a Personal Independence Payment claim in the Parliamentary Constituency of Preston in December 2014 and January 2015 who:</p><p>· have had an assessment by an assessment provider;</p><p>· are still waiting for an assessment by an assessment provider.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong> </strong></p></td><td><p><strong>December 2014</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>January 2015</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Total number of registrations</p></td><td><p>60</p></td><td><p>130</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Waiting for an assessment by an assessment provider</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Have had an assessment by an assessment provider</p></td><td><p>40</p></td><td><p>100</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Withdrawn or disallowed prior to a completed assessment by an assessment provider</p></td><td><p>20</p></td><td><p>30</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>Source: PIP Computer Systems</p><p> </p><p>Note that the figures above relate to:</p><ul><li>New claim registrations only. There were no DLA reassessment claims registered in these months.</li><li>Both claims made under special rules for the terminally ill and those under normal rules i.e. not the terminally ill.</li><li>Claims can be withdrawn by the claimant prior to an assessment by an assessment provider, or disallowed due to non-return of the PIP2 form within the time limit, failure to attend the assessment without good cause or failure of basic eligibility criteria (for example, age criteria, residence and presence).</li><li>Figures have been rounded to the nearest 10.</li></ul>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-06-29T14:02:02.887Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385152/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385152/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385152/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-23","Personal Independence Payment: Preston","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people in Preston constituency who applied for personal independence payments in (a) December 2014 and (b) January 2015 (i) have had medical assessments and (ii) are waiting for medical assessments.","false","Biography information for Sir Mark Hendrick","Preston","Mr Mark Hendrick","3670"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385153","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-29","<p /> <p>Information available on the number of Incapacity Benefit claimants currently awaiting a work capability assessment is published and can be found at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/employment-and-support-allowance-outcomes-of-work-capability-assessment" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/employment-and-support-allowance-outcomes-of-work-capability-assessment</a>.</p><p> </p><p>Official statistics for Incapacity Benefit Reassessment processing times are not readily available and to provide the information requested would incur disproportionate cost.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-06-29T13:56:34.94Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385153/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385153/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385153/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-23","Employment and Support Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many incapacity benefit claimants are awaiting an assessment for employment and support allowance; and how many such claimants have waited three months or more for that assessment.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","3646"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385154","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-29","<p /> <p>a) All staff directly employed by DWP and its arms length bodies are paid above the Living Wage.</p><p>b) DWP’s temporary agency staff are employed in line with Agency Workers Regulations which ensures parity with directly employed staff after 12 weeks.</p><p>c) There are currently 3,936 outsourced staff working for DWP contractors and their Service Partners who are paid at or below the Living Wage.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-06-29T13:36:40.683Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385154/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385154/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385154/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-23","Department for Work and Pensions: Living Wage","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many (a) direct employees, (b) agency staff and (c) outsourced staff working for his Department and its subsidiary agencies are paid less than the living wage.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","3647"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385155","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-29","<p>The total number of Short Term Benefit Advance applications received for:</p><p>a) January 2014 to December 2014 was 253,437. Of those 76,173 were successful.</p><p>b) the financial year April 2014 to February 2015 was 221,824. Of those 72,599 were sucessful.</p><p> </p><p><strong>Notes</strong></p><p>1. Only Employment and Support Allowance, Incapacity Benefit, Jobseekers Allowance and Income Support applications are included in the above information.</p><p> </p><p>2. A full set of data isn’t yet available for April 2014 to March 2015.</p><p> </p><p>3. Data for applications is sourced from clerical records via the Management Information System Programme (MISP) and awards sourced from the Benefit Expenditure Business Information system.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-06-29T13:02:06.897Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385155/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385155/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385155/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-23","Social Security Benefits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people applied for short term benefit advance in (a) 2014 and (b) 2014-15; and how many such applications were successful.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","3648"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385156","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-29","<p /> <p>All Jobcentre Plus staff have access to specific learning relating to the Armed Forces Covenant.</p><p> </p><p>This 30 minute learning product is part of foundation learning, undertaken at the beginning of the learning journey but is also accessible as “just in time” learning where staff may need to refresh their knowledge and understanding. The purpose of this learning is to prepare staff on how to assist Service leavers and their spouse or partner to resettle into civilian life and provides specific information relating to the Armed Forces Covenant.</p><p> </p><p>Additionally, to support people who are discharged from the armed forces on medical grounds, our network of Armed Forces Champions are available to help work coaches understand the range of support open to service leavers and to actively signpost to appropriate organisations.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-06-29T15:32:33.167Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385156/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385156/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385156/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-23","Jobcentre Plus: Armed Forces Covenant","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what training is given to Jobcentre Plus staff to take account of the Armed Forces Covenant.","false","Biography information for Andrew Bridgen","North West Leicestershire","Andrew Bridgen","3617"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385157","HM Treasury","false","2015-07-01","<p>Protecting women from violence is a key priority for the Government. We have strengthened the law in this area through the introduction of the Domestic Violence Disclosure Scheme and a number of new offences to protect victims. The annual Violence against Women and Girls report published by the Crown Prosecution Service on 25 June shows the number of convictions for domestic abuse have risen to their highest volume ever.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Marriage Allowance allows a basic rate taxpayer to transfer 10 per cent of their personal allowance to their spouse or civil partner. Only the transferor can make this transfer to their spouse or partner, and they can revoke this transfer at any point they wish.</p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2015-07-01T09:52:53.43Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385157/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385157/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385157/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2015-06-23","Married People: Tax Allowances","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the potential effect of the provision of the marriage allowance on the risks associated with domestic violence in relationships where a person is in receipt of that allowance.","false","Biography information for Rachael Maskell","York Central","Rachael Maskell","3618"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385158","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-29","<p /> <p>Information on the number of people in receipt of Disability Living Allowance, by parliamentary constituency and component, can be extracted using the DWP Tabtool: <a href="http://83.244.183.180/100pc/tabtool.html" target="_blank">http://83.244.183.180/100pc/tabtool.html</a></p><p><strong> </strong></p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","3808","2015-06-29T15:55:47.643Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385158/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385158/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385158/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-23","Disability Living Allowance: Barking and Dagenham","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people in the London Borough of Barking and Dagenham are in receipt of the mobility component of the disability living allowance.","false","Biography information for Dame Margaret Hodge","Barking","Margaret Hodge","3807"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385159","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-29","<p>Information on the number of people in receipt of Disability Living Allowance, by parliamentary constituency and component, can be extracted using the DWP Tabtool: <a href="http://83.244.183.180/100pc/tabtool.html" target="_blank">http://83.244.183.180/100pc/tabtool.html</a></p><p><strong> </strong></p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","3807","2015-06-29T15:55:47.737Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385159/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385159/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385159/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-23","Disability Living Allowance: Barking and Dagenham","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people in the London Borough of Barking and Dagenham are in receipt of disability living allowance at the (a) lower, (b) middle and (c) higher rates.","false","Biography information for Dame Margaret Hodge","Barking","Margaret Hodge","3808"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385160","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-29","<p /> <p>The information requested for those subject to the Removal of the Spare Room Subsidy in Torfaen, is not readily available and could only be provided at a disproportionate cost.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-06-29T13:40:06.813Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385160/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385160/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385160/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-23","Housing Benefit: Torfaen","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate he has made of the savings to the public purse arising from the under-occupancy penalty in Torfaen constituency in financial year 2014-15.","false","Biography information for Nick Thomas-Symonds","Torfaen","Nick Thomas-Symonds","3849"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385161","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-29","<p>DWP has written to individuals affected by State Pension age change and due to reach State Pension age by 2026, using the address details recorded by HMRC at the time.</p><p>DWP also makes information on State Pension age changes and who they affect available on Gov.uk, including the option to calculate State Pension age.</p><p>We have committed to completing a review of the State Pension age by May 2017. This is an important opportunity to ensure that State Pension age changes are fully considered by Government and well understood by those they affect.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","3827","2015-06-29T16:07:57.603Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385161/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385161/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385161/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-23","Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what further public information campaigns his Department plans to undertake on changes to the pension age.","false","Biography information for Stephen Gethins","North East Fife","Stephen Gethins","3828"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385162","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-29","<p /> <p>The information as requested is not available.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-06-29T13:27:08.067Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385162/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385162/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385162/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-23","Employment and Support Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many employment and support allowance claimants were affected by mandatory reconsideration in 2014-15; and how many such claimants waited 14 days or more to receive a decision following that consideration.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","3862"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385163","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-29","<p /> <p>DWP has written to individuals affected by State Pension age change and due to reach State Pension age by 2026, using the address details recorded by HMRC at the time.</p><p>DWP also makes information on State Pension age changes and who they affect available on Gov.uk, including the option to calculate State Pension age.</p><p>We have committed to completing a review of the State Pension age by May 2017. This is an important opportunity to ensure that State Pension age changes are fully considered by Government and well understood by those they affect.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","3828","2015-06-29T16:07:57.523Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385163/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385163/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385163/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-23","Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what direct notifications pensioners will receive of changes to the pension age.","false","Biography information for Stephen Gethins","North East Fife","Stephen Gethins","3827"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385164","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-29","<p /> <p>Information on mandatory reconsiderations of benefit decisions was released on 17<sup>th</sup> December 2014. This was an ad-hoc release of experimental statistics on MR requests made between 28<sup>th</sup>October 2013 and 31<sup>st</sup> October 2014. It gives an overview of mandatory reconsideration requests across all benefits recorded on DWP’s operational systems, and a focused summary on Employment and Support Allowance (ESA). This data can be found here:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/mandatory-reconsiderations-of-dwp-benefit-decisions-data-to-october-2014" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/mandatory-reconsiderations-of-dwp-benefit-decisions-data-to-october-2014</a></p><p> </p><p>DWP statisticians are looking to include statistics for the entire ESA Work Capability Assessment (WCA) process into the existing regular statistical publication, including information on Mandatory Reconsiderations outcomes. However before DWP is able to do this statisticians need to make sure that the data is accurate and fit for purpose and develop a robust methodology. When a decision has been made on improvements to the ESA WCA regular statistical publication we will pre-announce the improvements in accordance with the UKSA release protocols.</p><p> </p><p>The latest appeal statistics available, published by the Ministry of Justice, which includes data on ESA appeals received and cleared, can be found here at Tables 1.4 &amp; 2.7:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/tribunals-and-gender-recognition-certificate-statistics-quarterly-january-to-march-2015" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/tribunals-and-gender-recognition-certificate-statistics-quarterly-january-to-march-2015</a></p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-06-29T16:20:58.337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385164/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385164/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385164/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-23","Employment and Support Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what proportion of decisions on employment and support allowance applications have been overturned (a) at the mandatory reconsideration stage and (b) by tribunal in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","3836"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385165","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-07-01","<p /> <p>I refer the Rt Hon. Member to the answer I gave to his previous Question <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2015-06-09/1696/" target="_blank">UIN1696</a></p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-07-01T14:15:14.637Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385165/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385165/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385165/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-23","Housing Benefit: Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, which groups will be exempted from proposals to restrict housing benefit for 18 to 21 year olds.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","3817"
