"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385168","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-29","<p>Information on benefit expenditure for 2014/15 at a Parliamentary Constituency level is not currently available. 2014/15 data is planned for publication in September. Data for 2000/01 to 2013/14 is available via the following link:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/benefit-expenditure-and-caseload-tables-2014" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/benefit-expenditure-and-caseload-tables-2014</a></p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-06-29T13:32:43.323Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385168/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385168/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385168/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-23","Social Security Benefits: Torfaen","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what the cost to the public purse was of payment of (a) out-of-work and (b) in-work benefits to people in Torfaen constituency in financial year 2014-15.","false","Biography information for Nick Thomas-Symonds","Torfaen","Nick Thomas-Symonds","3903"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385169","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-29","<p>The Government’s commitment to reduce welfare spending was set out in its election manifesto. Further details will be given in due course.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-06-29T13:44:02.247Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385169/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385169/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385169/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-23","Social Security Benefits: Torfaen","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate he has made of the proportion of the Government's projected £12 billion reduction in welfare expenditure that will take place in Torfaen constituency.","false","Biography information for Nick Thomas-Symonds","Torfaen","Nick Thomas-Symonds","3904"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385170","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-06-29","<p /> <p>The information requested for those subject to the removal of the spare room subsidy for part a) is not readily available and could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p><p>The information requested for part (b) is not held.</p><p>However, an analysis of changes to the number of people subject to a reduction in their Housing Benefit award, including those who have downsized, from May to December 2013 was published here:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/removal-of-the-spare-room-subsidy-analysis-july-2014" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/removal-of-the-spare-room-subsidy-analysis-july-2014</a></p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-06-29T13:48:47.04Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385170/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385170/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/385170/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-06-23","Housing Benefit: Social Rented Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what proportion of people liable to the under-occupancy penalty (a) found alternative accommodation and (b) paid the penalty.","false","Biography information for Nick Thomas-Symonds","Torfaen","Nick Thomas-Symonds","3906"
